description:
&lt;p&gt;Due to the changes within respiratory /general medicine an opportunity has arisen recruit a band 6 sisters/charge nurse on a 12 month contract-either fixed term or secondment to drive this forward. We are looking for some-one who is committed, motivated and forward thinking to complement our existing team in achieving the best care for our patients receiving these treatments.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you are someone with strong leadership skills, and are keen to specialise in haematology this could be your opportunity to progress. As a band 6 sister/charge nurse your role will be providing treatments to our patients, co coordinating the day to day running of the ward safely and efficiently supporting and educating our junior nurses .&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further information please contact ward manager Lorraine Harwood or Fiona Verenakis&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;NameLorraine HarwoodJob titleUnit ManagerEmail addresslorraine.harwood@nhs.netTelephone number01253 953458Additional contact information&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Please contact Ward Manager Lorraine Harwood on 01253 953458 or Fiona Verenakis clinical matron via switchboard on 01253 300000 bleep 015 for further information.&lt;/p&gt;
